{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_61","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' PR_COMMENTS.md\"","aggregated_output":"This change addresses issue `#3464` by removing the key life-cycle terms from `UBERON:0000000 ! processual entity` and aligning them with `BFO:0000015 ! process`, which is the requested COB-compatible placement.\n\nChanges made:\n- reparented `UBERON:0000104 ! life cycle` from `UBERON:0000000 ! processual entity` to `BFO:0000015 ! process`\n- reparented `UBERON:0000105 ! life cycle stage` from `UBERON:0000000 ! processual entity` to `BFO:0000015 ! process`\n- added `term_tracker_item` links to issue `#3464` on the modified retained terms\n- obsoleted the unused temporal-boundary subtree:\n  - `UBERON:0035943 ! life cycle temporal boundary`\n  - `UBERON:0035944 ! life-death temporal boundary`\n  - `UBERON:0035945 ! start of life cycle`\n  - `UBERON:0035946 ! start of neonate stage`\n- added `consider: UBERON:0000071 ! death stage` for the obsolete death-boundary term\n- added `consider: UBERON:0007221 ! neonate stage` for the obsolete birth-boundary term\n- added `term_tracker_item` links to issue `#3464` on the obsoleted terms\n\nRationale:\n- The issue requested moving `life cycle` and `life cycle stage` under `process` rather than leaving them under the Uberon-specific `processual entity` class.\n- After that reparenting, the only remaining direct child in this local subtree was the `life cycle temporal boundary` branch.\n- The issue discussion notes that those temporal-boundary classes are unused vestiges of over-formalization, and no clear upper-level home for instantaneous boundary classes was established in Uberon.\n- Obsoleting that unused subtree is safer than guessing a new upper-level parent for abstract boundary classes.\n\nChecklist completed:\n- [x] read the imported issue context\n- [x] inspected the affected stanzas in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n- [x] checked parent consistency locally before